f(x)=Ce^{-2x}\implies f(0)=C
f(x)
f(0)=\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{\sqrt{t}}dt=\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-x^2}}{|x|}\,2x\,dx=2\int_{0}^{\infty}e^{-x^2}\,dx=\sqrt{\pi}.
f(x)=\sqrt{\pi}e^{-2x}.
